objects.name: cheeky chipmunk
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk is a malicious Microsoft Windows Remote Procedure Call (RPC) server malware. It is installed via a PowerShell loader and can be tasked by a separate standalone RPC client. The loader uses AMSI avoidance and layered obfuscation, encryption, and compression. Cheeky Chipmunk provides functionality such as executing shell commands, uploading and downloading files (facilitating data exfiltration and providing a vector for additional payloads), and maintains persistence as a Windows service. Communications occur over named pipes and can be configured for anonymous access. It employs multiple defense evasion techniques including masquerading as legitimate services and files, use of XOR obfuscation of import names, and self-deleting loader script.

objects.name: CheekyChipmunk_command_argument_check
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.

objects.name: CheekyChipmunk_GUID_bytes
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule CheekyChipmunk_GUID_bytes
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Detects the Cheeky Chipmunk RPC GUID"
        date = "2022-01-24"
        hash1 = "52c8cbd0545caab7596c1382c7fc5a479209851d"
        hash2 = "865f4c457bf86ff03456de828044f6ed6d6cf96a"
        hash3 = "5d5825b14377c5e5fe96816dd72a90bd13dc9fc8"
        hash4 = "7e4a6bac09ad214e98801bc199f96c265d7b6b48"

    strings:
        $GUID = {64 25 F0 7D 1E C3 68 4A A6 88 72 D0 EC 84 07 46}

    condition:
        uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
        uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
        all of them
}

objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.

rule CheekyChipmunk_control_handler_code
{
    meta:

handler"
        date = "2022-01-24"

    strings:
        $servicecode = {41 B8 01 00 00 00 33 D2 B9 03 00 00 00 E8 ?? ??
?? ?? E8 ?? ?? ?? ?? 45 33 C0 33 D2 B9 01 00 00 00 E8 ?? ?? ?? ?? EB ??
41 B8 01 00 00 00 33 D2 B9 06 00 00 00 E8 ?? ?? ?? ?? 45 33 C0 33 D2 B9
07 00 00 00 E8 ?? ?? ?? ?? EB ?? 41 B8 01 00 00 00 33 D2 B9 05 00 00 00
E8 ?? ?? ?? ?? 45 33 C0 33 D2 B9 04 00 00 00 E8 ?? ?? ?? ??}

    condition:
        uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
        uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
        all of them
}

rule CheekyChipmunk_amsi_avoidance_strings
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Detects Cheeky Chipmunk loader AMSI avoidance
strings"

        hash1 = "50c0bf9479efc93fa9cf1aa99bdca923273b71a1"

objects.name: CheekyChipmunk_xor_function_code
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule CheekyChipmunk_xor_function_code
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Detects Cheeky Chipmunk XOR function"
        date = "2022-01-24"
        hash1 = "52c8cbd0545caab7596c1382c7fc5a479209851d"

    strings:
        $funccode = {8B 44 24 04 48 8B 4C 24 20 0F B6 04 01 8B 0C 24 03
C8 8B C1 89 04 24 8B 44 24 04 48 8B 4C 24 20 0F B6 04 01 83 F0 55 8B 4C
24 04 48 8B 54 24 20 88 04 0A B8 01 00 00 00 48 6B C0 00 48 8B 4C 24 20
0F B6 04 01 8B 0C 24 03 C8 8B C1 89 04 24}

    condition:
        uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
        uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
        all of them
}

objects.name: CheekyChipmunk_print_format_strings
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule CheekyChipmunk_print_format_strings
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Detects Cheeky Chipmunk client print format
strings"

    strings:
        $SN = "0x%04d: SN %S: "
        $RC = "0x%04d: RC %S: "
        $EX = "0x%04d: EX %S: "
        $SNSuccess = "SN %S: success"
        $RCSuccess = "RC %S: success"

    condition:
        uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
        uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
        all of them
}

objects.name: Create or Modify System Process: Windows Service
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk maintains persistence by adding a new Windows service (pnrssp) for the RPC server component.

objects.name: Command and Scripting Interpreter: PowerShell
objects.description: Open-source PowerShell runner code is embedded in the Cheeky Chipmunk RPC server and used to invoke commands stored in the registry.

objects.name: Command and Scripting Interpreter: Windows Command Shell
objects.description: The Cheeky Chipmunk RPC server can be sent Windows shell commands by the RPC client.

objects.name: Inter-Process Communication: Component Object Model
objects.description: The Cheeky Chipmunk RPC server uses COM to call embedded PowerShell runner code.

objects.name: Windows Management Instrumentation
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk implements an RPC server to receive tasking.

objects.name: Deobfuscate/Decode Files or Information
objects.description: The Cheeky Chipmunk loader uses built-in and open-source PowerShell libraries to Base64-decode, 3DES-decrypt, and GZIP-decompress the RPC server.

objects.name: Indicator Removal on Host: File Deletion
objects.description: The Cheeky Chipmunk loader is deleted from disk once the RPC server is running. Cheeky Chipmunk deletes the log file containing details of its RPC server’s execution, following exfiltration.

objects.name: Masquerading: Match Legitimate Name or Location
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk masquerades as a legitimate Windows service path (netsvcs) to maintain persistence. The Cheeky Chipmunk log file (NTuser.log) is named similarly to a legitimate Windows log file (NTuser.dat.log). The Cheeky Chipmunk service (Peer Name Resolution Provider) is named similarly to a legitimate Windows service (Peer Name Resolution Protocol).

objects.name: Obfuscated Files or Information
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk’s import names are obfuscated by XORing with 0x55.

objects.name: Impair Defenses: Disable or Modify Tools
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk implements an AMSI bypass technique.

objects.name: Data from Local System
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk can be tasked to collect files.
